	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/b/ba/Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/b/ba/Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/b/ba/Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-kan.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div> 
<p>Although there are a number of ways to express "it depends" in Chinese, the most common ones in informal spoken Chinese involve the verb 看 (kàn). Some common expressions include 要看 (yào kàn) and 得看 (děi kàn). Both mean "(it) depends (on)." Literally, they would translate as "have to look at," so the logic is not hard to understand.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
